id: pm-eqk0
title: Prevent Decision items from entering agent work lanes by default; allow explicit maintainer opt-in
description: "Observed 2026-07-11: pm next recommends pm-pbyu (type Decision, ADR status proposed, priority 1) as THE recommended item, and pm claim --next would atomically claim it. ADR acceptance is a maintainer-only act (project convention: agents never flip ADRs), so an autonomous agent following the recommend-claim loop lands on an item it cannot resolve — a stalled lane, and at fleet scale every idle agent funnels into the same unresolvable Decision. The recommendation itself is informative (pm-pbyu + pm-bl8x gate 13 of 25 blocked items), so the fix is presentation + claim semantics, not ranking: Decisions belong in a decision-needed channel that names what they unblock, while the claimable recommendation stays actionable-by-agents. Complements closed pm-9x6k (dependency actionability) and pm-114v (atomic claim --next)."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: decisions,multi-agent,next,workflow
created_at: "2026-07-11T03:00:06.909Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-11T20:37:50.377Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-11T20:35:20.074Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: pm next surfaces open Decision-type items in a distinct decision-needed section (with what they gate) instead of as the claimable recommendation; pm claim --next skips Decision-type items unless an explicit opt-in flag is passed; behavior documented and covered by tests; existing recommendation ranking otherwise unchanged
risk: medium
confidence: medium
resolution: "Decisions appear in exactly one queue: decision_needed by default or claimable when opted in."
expected_result: Decision opt-in changes eligibility without duplicating output rows.
actual_result: includeDecisions empties decision_needed and ranks Decisions in the actionable queue.
