comments[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-11T03:06:49.578Z",maintainer-agent,"External confirmation (2026-07-11): GH-509 (pm-fjxm) independently requests the fleet worker loop this item protects — bounded candidate-walk on claim race loss. A walk WITHOUT the Decision-skip this item specifies makes the hazard strictly worse: every race loser advances down the ready queue and lands on the Decision item, so the funnel-into-one-ADR failure becomes the common path, not the unlucky one. pm-fjxm's AC references this item; sequencing preference: land eqk0's Decision-skip before or with fjxm's walk."
  "2026-07-11T18:21:07.424Z",codex-root,"Implementation start: active in one broad PR because GH-509 candidate filters/race walking, GH-513 ready ranking, and decision-needed separation share the public SDK actionability engine, claim transaction, CLI/MCP contracts, and fleet-worker verification. Live all-status search and full item/dependency/comment history confirmed no duplicate lineage; only these three items are active."
  "2026-07-11T18:28:48.470Z",codex-root,"Implementation checkpoint: Decision items are separated into decision_needed with downstream unblocks context; agent recommendation/claim skips them by default and include-decisions provides explicit maintainer opt-in."
  "2026-07-11T19:28:30.645Z",codex-root,"Final evidence: focused command/SDK suites pass; full repository coverage passes 5550/5550 at exact 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines; pnpm lint passes ESLint, zero jscpd clones, static quality, 100% docstrings, and token-budget gates; contracts, docs/skills, secret scan, and dependency audit pass. Fresh packed-package temp workspace proves filtered rank 1 selection and bounded atomic claim return the same task."
  "2026-07-11T20:03:15.161Z",codex-root,"Bot review start: Gemini found includeDecisions duplicated Decision rows between claimable and decision_needed projections. Reopened for fix."
  "2026-07-11T20:06:37.902Z",codex-root,"Review fix implemented: includeDecisions moves Decisions into the claimable queue instead of duplicating them in decision_needed; regression assertion passes."
  "2026-07-11T20:35:16.203Z",codex-root,"Final review evidence: Decision rows are excluded from held_by_others by default and remain exclusive to decision_needed; opt-in restores claim ownership filtering. Changelog wording now states default exclusion and authorized opt-in. Focused 294 tests and strict lint/static gates pass."
